name: AJ Lee
bio: Nerdy character who became a three-time Divas Champion and was married to CM Punk.

name: Adam Cole
bio: Former leader of The Elite and multi-time champion across ROH, NXT, and AEW who defines modern wrestling.

name: Akira Taue
bio: Four Pillars of Heaven member known for his chokeslam and being the tallest of the group.

name: Al Snow
bio: Hardcore legend known for his mannequin head prop and J.O.B. Squad leadership.

name: Albert
bio: Large athlete known for his agility and partnerships with Test and X-Pac.

name: Alberto Del Rio
bio: Mexican aristocrat who captured multiple world championships with his technical wrestling skills.

name: Alexa Bliss
bio: Former gymnast who became the first woman to hold both Raw and SmackDown Women's Championships.

name: Alexander Volkanovski
bio: Alexander Volkanovski is a former UFC Featherweight Champion known for his exceptional cardio, boxing skills, and fight IQ. Despite being one of the shorter fighters in his division, Volkanovski's well-rounded skill set and relentless pressure made him nearly unbeatable. His trilogy with Max Holloway is considered one of the best in featherweight history.

name: Amanda Nunes
bio: Amanda Lourenço Nunes is a Brazilian mixed martial artist.

name: Anderson Silva
bio: Anderson Silva is widely regarded as one of the greatest mixed martial artists of all time. The former UFC Middleweight Champion holds the longest title reign in UFC history at 2,457 days. Known for his precision striking, creativity, and incredible reflexes, Silva dominated the middleweight division for over 6 years.

name: Andre the Giant
nickname: The Eighth Wonder of the World
bio: The most famous giant in wrestling history and one of the first global wrestling superstars.

name: Apollo Crews
bio: Incredible athlete known for his amazing strength and gorilla press slam.

name: Arn Anderson
bio: Four Horsemen enforcer and wrestling legend known for the greatest spine buster in the business.

name: Asuka
bio: Japanese submission specialist with an undefeated streak of 914 days across NXT and main roster.

name: BJ Penn
bio: BJ Penn was the first fighter to win UFC titles in two different weight classes. Known for his exceptional boxing, Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu skills, and natural fighting ability, Penn was dominant in both the lightweight and welterweight divisions. He was inducted into the UFC Hall of Fame in 2015.

name: Bam Bam Bigelow
bio: Agile big man known for his flame tattoos and surprising athleticism for his size.

name: Baron Corbin
bio: Former NFL player and Golden Gloves boxer turned wrestler.

name: Batista
bio: The Animal who became a main event star as part of Evolution before going Hollywood.

name: Bayley
bio: The hugger turned role model who captured hearts and championships.

name: Becky Lynch
bio: The Man who became the face of the women's evolution in WWE.

name: Beth Phoenix
bio: Powerhouse wrestler married to Edge who dominated with strength and technical skill.

name: Bianca Belair
bio: The EST of WWE who represents strength, speed, and athleticism in women's wrestling.

name: Big Boss Man
bio: Prison guard turned wrestler who brought law enforcement attitude to sports entertainment.

name: Big E
bio: Powerlifting champion and New Day member who achieved his championship dreams.

name: Big Show
bio: The World's Largest Athlete who has been a giant presence in wrestling for nearly three decades.

name: Billy Kidman
bio: Three-time WCW Cruiserweight Champion known for his innovative Shooting Star Press.

name: Blackjack Mulligan
bio: Texas cowboy and patriarch of the Windham wrestling family, including sons Barry and Kendall.

name: Blue Demon
bio: Santo's greatest rival and Mexico's second most famous luchador.

name: Bob Backlund
bio: Clean-cut All-American hero who held the WWWF Championship for nearly 6 years.

name: Bobby Lashley
bio: Military veteran and mixed martial artist who proved his all mighty dominance in WWE.

name: Bobo Brazil
bio: Pioneering African American wrestler who broke barriers across multiple territories.

name: Booker T
bio: Five-time WCW World Heavyweight Champion and WWE Hall of Famer with a legendary career spanning decades.

name: Braun Strowman
bio: Massive powerhouse known for flipping over cars and ambulances in his feuds.

name: Bret Hart
bio: Excellence of execution and technical wrestling master from the legendary Hart wrestling family.

name: Brie Bella
bio: Daniel Bryan's wife and Nikki's twin who formed the Bella Twins and was Divas Champion.

name: British Bulldog
bio: Powerhouse from England who won the Intercontinental Title at SummerSlam 1992 in his home country.

name: Brock Lesnar
bio: The Beast Incarnate who conquered UFC and WWE, bringing legitimacy and intensity to sports entertainment.

name: Bronson Reed
bio: Australian powerhouse known for incredible athleticism despite his massive size.

name: Bruno Sammartino
bio: The longest-reigning WWE Champion in history, holding the title for over 11 years combined across two reigns.

name: Buddy Rogers
bio: The original 'Nature Boy' and first WWWF Champion, setting the template for wrestling superstars.

name: Bull Buchanan
bio: Tag team specialist known for partnering with Boss Man and Goodfather.

name: CM Punk
bio: The straight-edge superstar with the longest WWE Championship reign of the modern era at 434 days.

name: CM Punk (ROH)
tagline: Straight Edge Means Better Than You
bio: ROH World Champion who built his legendary career in Ring of Honor before conquering WWE and AEW.

name: Cactus Jack
bio: Mick Foley's most extreme persona, known for his death-defying hardcore matches.

name: Carla Esparza
bio: Carla Esparza was the first-ever UFC Women's Strawweight Champion, winning the inaugural title on The Ultimate Fighter. Known for her wrestling and grappling skills, she reclaimed the title years later, becoming a two-time champion and one of the division's most accomplished fighters.

name: Carlito
bio: Cool Puerto Rican who returned to WWE after years away, still spitting apple and taking names.

name: Carmelo Hayes
bio: Smooth operator from Massachusetts who dominated NXT with his athletic ability and confidence.

name: Cesaro
bio: Incredibly strong technical wrestler known for his swing and uppercuts.

name: Chad Gable
bio: Olympic amateur wrestling standout who became a technical master in WWE.

name: Charlotte Flair
bio: Ric Flair's daughter and the most decorated women's champion in modern WWE.

name: Chief Jay Strongbow
bio: Native American character who performed war dances and was a four-time WWE Tag Team Champion.

name: Chris Benoit
bio: Technical wrestling master and WCW World Heavyweight Champion known for his incredible in-ring ability.

name: Chris Jericho
bio: First Undisputed Champion, King of the World, and Ayatollah of Rock and Rolla.

name: Chuck Liddell
bio: Chuck Liddell was one of the first UFC superstars and helped bring mixed martial arts into the mainstream. Known for his knockout power, takedown defense, and exciting fighting style, Liddell was the face of the UFC during its explosive growth period in the mid-2000s.

name: Chyna
nickname: The Ninth Wonder of the World
bio: The Ninth Wonder of the World who broke barriers competing against men.

name: Cody Rhodes
bio: The American Nightmare who finished his story by capturing the WWE Championship at WrestleMania 40.

name: Conor McGregor
bio: Conor Anthony McGregor is an Irish professional mixed martial artist.

name: Crash Holly
bio: Hardcore division mainstay known for claiming to weigh over 400 pounds.

name: Cris Cyborg
bio: Cris Cyborg is widely considered one of the greatest women's featherweights of all time. Known for her aggressive striking and knockout power, she held titles in Strikeforce, Invicta FC, UFC, and Bellator. Her 13-year unbeaten streak established her as one of the most feared fighters in women's MMA.

name: Curt Hennig
bio: WWE Intercontinental Champion who joined the nWo and became a WCW legend in his own right.

name: Curtis Axel
bio: Third generation wrestler, son of Mr. Perfect Curt Hennig.

name: D-Lo Brown
bio: High-energy performer known for his head-shake entrance and European Championship reigns.

name: Dakota Kai
bio: New Zealand striker who became a fan favorite with her resilient underdog story.

name: Damian Priest
bio: Puerto Rican powerhouse who reached the pinnacle by capturing the World Heavyweight Championship.

name: Damien Sandow
bio: Intellectual character known for his Money in the Bank cash-in attempt.

name: Daniel Bryan
bio: The ultimate underdog who captured the WWE Championship at WrestleMania 30 in a legendary moment.

name: Daniel Bryan (ROH)
bio: ROH World Champion and WWE legend who showcased pure wrestling excellence in Ring of Honor.

name: Daniel Cormier
bio: Daniel Cormier is a former two-division UFC champion and Olympic wrestler. Known for his incredible wrestling credentials and determination, DC captured both the light heavyweight and heavyweight titles. His rivalries with Jon Jones and Stipe Miocic produced some of the most memorable fights in UFC history. After retiring, he became a successful commentator for UFC events.

name: David Von Erich
bio: Youngest of the Von Erich wrestling dynasty, considered the most naturally talented.

name: Dean Malenko
bio: Technical wrestling master and four-time WCW Cruiserweight Champion known for his submission expertise.

name: Demolition
bio: Face-painted powerhouse team that dominated WWE's tag division in the late 1980s.

name: Diamond Dallas Page
bio: WCW World Heavyweight Champion who pioneered the Diamond Cutter and created DDP Yoga.

name: Dick Murdoch
bio: Legendary tag team wrestler and singles competitor across multiple territories.

name: Diesel
bio: Big Daddy Cool who held the WWE Championship for nearly a full year during the New Generation Era.

name: Dolph Ziggler
bio: Amateur wrestler turned sports entertainer known for his incredible athleticism.

name: Dominik Mysterio
bio: Rey Mysterio's son who turned heel and became one of WWE's most hated villains with The Judgment Day.

name: Dory Funk Jr.
bio: Four-year NWA World Heavyweight Champion from wrestling's first family.

name: Dr. Britt Baker
bio: Former AEW Women's World Champion who transformed from face to heel and became the ace of AEW's women's division.

name: Drew McIntyre
bio: Scottish Warrior who fought his way back to the top to become WWE Champion during the pandemic era.

name: Droz
bio: Former NFL player whose career was cut short due to an in-ring injury.

name: Dusty Rhodes
bio: The son of a plumber who became wrestling royalty. Three-time NWA World Heavyweight Champion and the voice of the common man.

name: Dynamite Kid
bio: Innovative high-flyer who formed the British Bulldogs and influenced modern wrestling style.

name: Eddie Guerrero
bio: Latino Heat who lied, cheated, and stole his way into the hearts of fans worldwide.

name: Edge
bio: The Ultimate Opportunist who cashed in Money in the Bank contracts and won 11 world championships.

name: Edge & Christian
bio: Childhood friends who became 7-time Tag Team Champions in WWE's golden era of tag teams.

name: El Santo
bio: The most iconic luchador in history, known for his silver mask and film career.

name: Ernie Ladd
tagline: From the NFL to the Wrestling Ring
bio: Former NFL player who became a dominant heel across multiple territories.

name: Ethan Page
bio: Veteran performer who brought his 'All Ego' persona from AEW to capture the NXT Championship.

name: Evander Holyfield
bio: Evander Holyfield is the only four-time heavyweight champion in history. He successfully moved up from cruiserweight to heavyweight and defeated Mike Tyson twice, including the infamous 'Bite Fight.' Known for his heart, determination, and warrior spirit.

name: Eve Torres
bio: Former model and dancer who became a three-time Divas Champion.

name: Fabulous Moolah
bio: Longest-reigning champion in WWE history, holding the Women's Championship for 28 years combined.

name: Fedor Emelianenko
bio: Fedor Emelianenko is widely considered the greatest heavyweight mixed martial artist of all time. Dominant in PRIDE FC for nearly a decade, Fedor was known for his calm demeanor, incredible hand speed for a heavyweight, and submission skills. He went undefeated for over 9 years.

name: Finn Balor
bio: Irish wrestler and first Universal Champion who transforms into The Demon for big matches.

name: Floyd Mayweather Jr.
bio: Floyd Mayweather Jr. retired undefeated with a perfect 50-0 record. Known for his defensive genius, precise counter-punching, and business acumen, Mayweather won world titles in five weight divisions and became the highest-paid athlete in sports history.

name: Forrest Griffin
bio: Forrest Griffin was the winner of the first season of The Ultimate Fighter reality show, which helped launch the UFC into mainstream popularity. Known for his heart, determination, and fan-friendly fighting style, Griffin became a UFC champion and Hall of Famer.

name: Fritz Von Erich
bio: WCCW founder and patriarch of wrestling's most tragic family.

name: Gail Kim
bio: Talented high-flyer who made history as the first Asian Women's Champion in WWE.

name: George Foreman
bio: George Foreman had two distinct careers - dominating the 1970s as a feared puncher, then making an incredible comeback in the 1990s to become the oldest heavyweight champion ever at age 45. His knockout power was legendary, and his grilling empire made him a household name.

name: Georges St-Pierre
bio: Georges St-Pierre is considered one of the greatest welterweights and pound-for-pound fighters of all time. A two-division UFC champion, GSP was known for his incredible athleticism, game planning, and well-rounded skill set. He successfully defended the welterweight title 9 times.

name: Germaine de Randamie
bio: Germaine de Randamie was the inaugural UFC Women's Featherweight Champion, known for her elite kickboxing background. A former kickboxing world champion, she brought high-level striking to women's MMA and was one of the pioneers of the featherweight division.

name: Giovanni Vinci
bio: Italian powerhouse who formed a dominant tag team partnership with Ludwig Kaiser.

name: Godfather
bio: Pimp character known for his ho train and entertaining entrance.

name: Goldberg
bio: WCW's monster with an incredible 173-match winning streak and one of wrestling's most dominant forces.

name: Gorilla Monsoon
bio: Legendary wrestler turned beloved commentator whose voice defined WWE for generations of fans.

name: Greg Valentine
bio: Technical submission specialist who mastered the Figure Four and was managed by Jimmy Hart.

name: Gunther
bio: Austrian powerhouse who dominated NXT UK and became the longest-reigning Intercontinental Champion in modern WWE.

name: Hacksaw Jim Duggan
bio: Patriotic brawler who carried a 2x4 board and shouted 'USA!' while winning the first King of the Ring.

name: Hangman Adam Page
bio: Former AEW World Heavyweight Champion who completed the greatest character arc in modern wrestling.

name: Hardcore Holly
bio: Tough veteran known for his hard-hitting style and NASCAR racing gimmick.

name: Harlem Heat
bio: Ten-time WCW Tag Team Champions and one of the most dominant tag teams in WCW history.

name: Harley Race
bio: Eight-time NWA World Heavyweight Champion. One of the toughest and most respected wrestlers in history.

name: Hart Foundation
nickname: The Excellence of Execution & The Anvil
bio: Technical excellence combined with raw power made them one of the greatest tag teams ever.

name: High Chief Peter Maivia
bio: Samoan wrestling royalty and The Rock's grandfather who brought Polynesian culture to American wrestling.

name: Hirooki Goto
bio: Samurai-inspired wrestler known for never winning the top title despite many attempts.

name: Hiroshi Hase
bio: Olympic amateur wrestler who became a legend in both NJPW and AJPW.

name: Hiroshi Tanahashi
bio: Eight-time IWGP Heavyweight Champion and New Japan legend who carried the company during its rebuilding years.

name: Holly Holm
bio: Holly Holm shocked the world by ending Ronda Rousey's undefeated streak with a devastating head kick knockout. A former professional boxer with an 18-fight winning streak, Holm brought elite striking to women's MMA. She's one of the few fighters to hold titles in both boxing and MMA.

name: Hollywood Hogan
bio: The leader of the nWo who shocked the wrestling world by turning heel and joining the black and white.

name: Hulk Hogan
bio: Terry Eugene Bollea, better known by his ring name Hulk Hogan, is an American retired professional wrestler.

name: IYO SKY
bio: Japanese wrestling prodigy and former WWE Women's Champion with incredible technical skills.

name: Ilja Dragunov
bio: Intense Russian-German wrestler known for his unmatched intensity and emotional matches.

name: Islam Makhachev
bio: Islam Makhachev is the current UFC Lightweight Champion and a dominant wrestler from Dagestan. Training alongside Khabib Nurmagomedov, Islam combines elite wrestling with improved striking to control his opponents. His rise to the top of the lightweight division has been methodical and impressive, carrying on the legacy of Dagestani dominance in MMA.

name: Ivan Koloff
bio: The man who ended Bruno Sammartino's first legendary title reign at Madison Square Garden.

name: Ivan Putski
bio: Powerlifting strongman from Poland who brought European style to American wrestling in the 1970s-80s.

name: Ivory
bio: Member of Right to Censor who became a three-time Women's Champion in the Attitude Era.

name: JBL
bio: Self-proclaimed Wrestling God who held the WWE Championship for 280 days as a despised heel.

name: JD McDonagh
bio: Technical wrestler from Ireland and member of The Judgment Day faction.

name: Jack Brisco
bio: Two-time NWA World Heavyweight Champion with legitimate amateur wrestling credentials.

name: Jackie Fargo
bio: Memphis wrestling legend known for his strut and being Jerry Lawler's mentor.

name: Jacob Fatu
bio: High-flying super heavyweight from the Anoa'i family who shocked WWE by joining The Bloodline.

name: Jacqueline
bio: First African-American WWE Women's Champion and tough competitor who broke barriers.

name: Jade Cargill
bio: Undefeated powerhouse who transferred from AEW to WWE as one of the most dominant women's wrestlers.

name: Jake Roberts
bio: Master psychologist who never needed championships, brought snakes to the ring and invented the DDT.

name: Jazz
bio: Tough competitor known for her hardcore style and ECW background.

name: Je'Von Evans
bio: Rising young star with incredible athletic ability and high-flying offense making waves in NXT.

name: Jerry Lawler
tagline: It's Good to Be the King
bio: Memphis wrestling royalty and longtime WWE commentator with over 160 championship reigns.

name: Jerry Lynn
bio: Gifted technical wrestler who had classic matches with RVD and became ECW's final champion.

name: Jessica Andrade
bio: Jessica Andrade is known for her incredible power and relentless pressure despite her smaller stature. A former UFC Women's Strawweight Champion, she's competed successfully across multiple weight classes and is known for her devastating knockout power and granite chin.

name: Jimmy Hart
bio: Wrestling manager extraordinaire who started as a wrestler in Memphis.

name: Joanna Jedrzejczyk
bio: Joanna Jedrzejczyk was one of the most dominant UFC Women's Strawweight Champions, known for her elite Muay Thai striking and volume. The former champion defended her title five times and was involved in some of the greatest women's fights in UFC history, including her wars with Zhang Weili.

name: Joe Frazier
bio: Joe Frazier was the first man to defeat Muhammad Ali and held the undisputed heavyweight championship from 1970-1973. Known for his relentless pressure, devastating left hook, and incredible heart, Frazier engaged in one of boxing's greatest rivalries with Ali.

name: John Cena
bio: John Felix Anthony Cena Jr. is an American professional wrestler, actor, and former rapper currently signed to WWE.

name: Jon Jones
bio: Jonathan Dwight Jones is an American professional mixed martial artist.

name: Jon Moxley
bio: AEW World Heavyweight Champion and hardcore legend who left WWE to become the face of AEW.

name: Judy Martin
bio: Half of The Glamour Girls tag team and women's wrestling pioneer.

name: Junkyard Dog
bio: Beloved babyface who danced to 'Grab Them Cakes' and was the first major African-American star in WWE.

name: Justin Credible
bio: Cocky heel who became ECW's final champion before the company's closure.

name: Kaitlyn
bio: Bodybuilder and former NXT winner who brought power and athleticism to the Divas division.

name: Kamala
bio: Savage giant managed by classy Freddie Blassie who terrorized WWE in the 1980s and 1990s.

name: Kane
bio: The Undertaker's demonic half-brother who terrorized WWE for over two decades.

name: Katsuyori Shibata
bio: Hard-hitting shooter who had to retire due to injury after a legendary match with Okada.

name: Kazuchika Okada
bio: Seven-time IWGP Heavyweight Champion and the ace of New Japan Pro Wrestling with legendary matches.

name: Kelly Kelly
bio: Former gymnast and model who became Divas Champion and was a fan favorite in the late 2000s.

name: Ken Patera
bio: Olympic weightlifter who transitioned to pro wrestling and held the Intercontinental Title for over a year.

name: Kenny Omega
bio: Former AEW World Heavyweight Champion and leader of The Elite. Considered by many as the best wrestler in the world.

name: Kenta Kobashi
bio: Four Pillars of Heaven member known for his incredible toughness and legendary burning hammer finisher.

name: Kerry Von Erich
bio: NWA World Heavyweight Champion and WWE Intercontinental Champion from wrestling's most famous family.

name: Kevin Nash
bio: Big Sexy and founding member of the nWo who dominated the main event scene in both promotions.

name: Kevin Owens
bio: Former ROH and WWE champion who built his reputation in independent wrestling as Kevin Steen.

name: Khabib Nurmagomedov
bio: Khabib Nurmagomedov retired as the undefeated UFC Lightweight Champion with a perfect 29-0 record. Known for his dominant wrestling, ground control, and incredible pressure, Khabib never lost a round in any of his UFC title fights. His rivalry with Conor McGregor was one of the biggest in UFC history.

name: King Kong Bundy
bio: Massive heel who demanded five-count pins and headlined WrestleMania 2 against Hulk Hogan.

name: Kofi Kingston
bio: Feel-good champion who captured the WWE Championship at WrestleMania 35 in an emotional victory.

name: Koko B. Ware
bio: High-flying entertainer who brought his pet bird Frankie to the ring and was inducted into WWE Hall of Fame.

name: Kurt Angle
bio: Olympic gold medalist who became one of the greatest technical wrestlers in WWE history.

name: LA Knight
bio: Charismatic performer who became a breakout star with his infectious personality and catchphrases.

name: La Parka
bio: Iconic skeleton-costumed luchador who became a cult favorite in WCW.

name: Lance Storm
bio: Technical wrestler known for his serious demeanor and championship collecting in WCW.

name: Layla
bio: British dancer who formed the LayCool team with Michelle McCool and held multiple titles.

name: Leilani Kai
tagline: Island Beauty with a Mean Streak
bio: WWE Women's Champion and longtime veteran of women's wrestling.

name: Lex Luger
bio: WCW World Heavyweight Champion and former bodybuilder who was the face of WCW in the early 90s.

name: Lita
bio: Revolutionary high-flying daredevil who changed women's wrestling forever.

name: Liv Morgan
bio: Resilient competitor who overcame early career struggles to become a two-time women's champion.

name: Ludwig Kaiser
bio: German technician and Gunther's loyal partner who excels in tag team competition.

name: Lyoto Machida
bio: Lyoto Machida brought traditional karate to MMA with devastating effectiveness. Known for his elusive movement, counter-striking, and unique karate-based style, Machida was nearly unbeatable during his prime. His knockout of Rashad Evans is considered one of the greatest in UFC history.

name: MJF
bio: AEW World Heavyweight Champion and generational heel who represents the future of professional wrestling.

name: Madusa
bio: WCW Women's Champion who famously threw the WWE Women's Championship in the trash on Monday Nitro.

name: Mae Young
bio: Wrestling pioneer who competed for nearly 70 years and remained active into her 80s.

name: Manny Pacquiao
bio: Manny Pacquiao is the only boxer to win world titles in eight different weight divisions. Known for his explosive power, relentless pace, and incredible heart, Pacquiao became a global icon and national hero in the Philippines. His rivalry with Floyd Mayweather captivated the boxing world.

name: Mark Henry
bio: Olympic weightlifter turned wrestler, holder of multiple powerlifting world records.

name: Mark William Calaway
bio: The Undertaker is one of WWE's most iconic and respected performers, known for his supernatural character and legendary WrestleMania streak. With a career spanning over three decades, Taker evolved from a zombie-like mortician to the American Badass and back, always maintaining his status as WWE's conscience and locker room leader.

name: Marloes Coenen
bio: Marloes Coenen was a pioneer of women's MMA and former Strikeforce Women's Bantamweight Champion. With a career spanning over 16 years, she was one of the most experienced women fighters and helped pave the way for the current generation of female athletes in MMA.

name: Maryse
bio: French-Canadian model who became a two-time Divas Champion before managing The Miz.

name: Matt Hughes
bio: Matt Hughes was one of the most dominant welterweight champions in UFC history. Known for his incredible strength, wrestling ability, and ground-and-pound, Hughes successfully defended the welterweight title 7 times and was inducted into the UFC Hall of Fame in 2010.

name: Melina
bio: Former model and manager who became a five-time champion known for her flexibility.

name: Mercedes Mone
bio: Former WWE Women's Champion who became NJPW Strong Women's Champion, revolutionizing women's wrestling worldwide.

name: Michelle McCool
bio: Former teacher who became the first Divas Champion and formed LayCool with Layla.

name: Mick Foley
bio: Mick Foley is a hardcore wrestling legend known for his three distinct personas: Cactus Jack, Mankind, and Dude Love. His willingness to put his body on the line in extreme matches, combined with his exceptional mic skills and writing ability, made him one of the most beloved figures in wrestling. His Hell in a Cell match with The Undertaker is iconic.

name: Mickie James
bio: Country music recording artist and five-time Women's Champion with incredible longevity.

name: Mideon
bio: Ministry of Darkness member known for his bizarre naked phase.

name: Miesha Tate
bio: Miesha Tate was a pioneer of women's MMA and played a crucial role in the sport's growth. A former UFC and Strikeforce champion, she was known for her wrestling background, heart, and never-give-up attitude. Her rivalries with Ronda Rousey helped bring women's MMA to the mainstream.

name: Mike Tyson
bio: Mike Tyson became the youngest heavyweight champion in history at age 20. Known for his ferocious power, intimidating presence, and explosive knockout ability, Tyson dominated the late 1980s heavyweight division. His personal troubles and prison sentence interrupted what could have been an even more dominant career.

name: Mikey Whipwreck
bio: Underdog fan favorite who overcame his small stature to become a triple crown winner.

name: Mitsuharu Misawa
bio: Four Pillars of Heaven leader and arguably Japan's greatest wrestler. Tragically died in the ring in 2009.

name: Molly Holly
bio: Technical wrestler who was part of the Holly family and known for her wholesome character.

name: Money Inc.
nickname: The Million Dollar Man & The Tax Man
bio: Corporate villains who combined wealth and tax expertise to dominate early 1990s WWE.

name: Mr. Perfect
bio: Perfectionist wrestler who never lost his smile and was considered one of the best technical wrestlers ever.

name: Muhammad Ali
bio: Muhammad Ali is widely regarded as the greatest heavyweight boxer of all time. Known for his lightning-fast footwork, powerful jab, and psychological warfare, Ali was a three-time heavyweight champion who transcended sports to become a global icon. His fights with Joe Frazier, George Foreman, and Sonny Liston are legendary.

name: Natalya
bio: Third generation Hart family wrestler known for her technical ability.

name: New Jack
bio: Hardcore brawler known for his wild weapon-filled matches and Natural Born Killaz entrance.

name: Nia Jax
bio: Samoan powerhouse and cousin of The Rock who dominated the women's division with her size advantage.

name: Nicco Montano
bio: Nicco Montano was the inaugural UFC Women's Flyweight Champion, winning the title on The Ultimate Fighter reality show. Though her championship reign was brief, she made history as the first flyweight champion and helped establish the 125-pound division in women's MMA.

name: Nick Bockwinkel
bio: Four-time AWA World Heavyweight Champion known for his technical wrestling and articulate promos.

name: Nikki Bella
bio: Twin sister who became the longest-reigning Divas Champion in modern history at 301 days.

name: Orange Cassidy
bio: AEW International Champion who revolutionized wrestling with his unique comedy-based character and surprising athleticism.

name: Owen Hart
bio: Technical wrestling genius and Hart family member who tragically died in a wrestling accident.

name: Ox Baker
bio: Menacing heel known for his wild appearance and the Heart Punch finisher.

name: Paige
bio: British wrestling royalty who became the youngest Divas Champion and started the women's revolution.

name: Papa Shango
bio: Mystical voodoo practitioner who cast spells and curses on his opponents in early 1990s WWE.

name: Pedro Morales
bio: First Triple Crown Champion in WWE history, beloved by fans worldwide.

name: Pentagon Jr.
bio: Lucha Underground legend and AEW star known for his incredible character work and arm-breaking prowess.

name: Pete Dunne
bio: Brutal British wrestler known for his hard-hitting style and finger manipulation.

name: Prince Albert
bio: Intimidating big man known for his body piercings and association with Boss Man.

name: Psicosis
bio: High-flying luchador who was part of the legendary WCW cruiserweight division.

name: Quinton Jackson
bio: Quinton 'Rampage' Jackson was known for his explosive knockout power, entertaining personality, and successful crossover into acting. A former UFC and PRIDE champion, Rampage was one of the biggest stars in MMA and helped bring the sport to mainstream audiences.

name: Randy Couture
bio: Randy Couture is a UFC Hall of Famer and one of the few fighters to win titles in two weight classes. Known for his wrestling background, 'dirty boxing' in the clinch, and incredible longevity, Couture competed at the highest level well into his 40s and was a five-time UFC champion.

name: Randy Orton
bio: Third-generation superstar and youngest World Heavyweight Champion in WWE history.

name: Randy Savage
bio: Colorful superstar known for his flamboyant personality, 'Oh yeah!' catchphrase, and relationship with Miss Elizabeth.

name: Raquel Rodriguez
bio: Towering Texan who dominated NXT before making her mark on the main roster.

name: Raven
bio: Hardcore legend who led The Flock and became a cult favorite in both ECW and WCW.

name: Razor Ramon
bio: Cuban chain-wearing bad guy who created ladder match history and co-founded the nWo.

name: Rey Fenix
bio: AEW Tag Team Champion and lucha libre legend known for incredible high-flying moves and innovative offense.

name: Rey Mysterio
bio: The biggest little man in wrestling history, inspiring underdogs everywhere.

name: Rey Mysterio Jr.
bio: Legendary lucha libre wrestler who revolutionized the cruiserweight division in WCW and became a WWE Hall of Famer.

name: Rey Mysterio Sr.
bio: Lucha libre legend and uncle of Rey Mysterio Jr., pioneer of high-flying style.

name: Rhea Ripley
bio: Dominant Australian powerhouse who has become one of the top stars in modern WWE.

name: Ric Flair
bio: The stylin', profilin', limousine riding, jet flying, kiss-stealin', wheelin' dealin' son of a gun! Woooo!

name: Rick Rude
bio: Arrogant heel who insulted audiences and was part of historic Monday Night War controversy.

bio: Technical wrestling master and NWA World Heavyweight Champion with classic feuds.

name: Ricochet

name: Road Dogg

name: Rob Van Dam

name: Roberto Duran
bio: Roberto Duran was a ferocious fighter who won world titles in four weight divisions during a career that spanned five decades. Known for his granite chin, devastating body shots, and intimidating persona, Duran's rivalry with Sugar Ray Leonard produced some of boxing's greatest fights.

name: Roman Reigns
bio: The Tribal Chief who has acknowledged his position as the head of the table in WWE.

name: Ron Garvin
bio: NWA World Heavyweight Champion known for his tough guy persona and boxing background.

name: Ronda Rousey
bio: UFC Hall of Famer who brought mainstream attention and legitimacy to women's wrestling.

name: Rose Namajunas
bio: Rose Namajunas is a two-time UFC Women's Strawweight Champion known for her well-rounded skills and mental toughness. She shocked the world by knocking out Joanna Jedrzejczyk to win her first title and has been involved in some of the most technical women's fights in UFC history.

name: Royce Gracie
bio: Royce Gracie revolutionized martial arts by winning the first, second, and fourth UFC tournaments despite being the smallest competitor. He introduced Brazilian Jiu-Jitsu to the world and proved that technique could overcome size and strength. Royce is a UFC Hall of Famer and MMA pioneer.

name: Rusev
bio: Former MMA fighter turned wrestler with a patriotic Bulgarian character.

name: Ryback
bio: Powerhouse known for his 'Feed Me More' catchphrase and Goldberg-like entrance.

name: Sabu
bio: Extreme high-flyer known for putting himself through tables and his barbed wire matches.

name: Sami Zayn

name: Samoa Joe
bio: ROH World Champion and submission specialist who dominated independent wrestling before WWE and AEW success.

name: Sandman
bio: ECW's beer-drinking, cigarette-smoking antihero known for his Singapore cane and Enter Sandman entrance.

name: Sarah Kaufman
bio: Sarah Kaufman was one of the early stars of women's MMA and a former Strikeforce Women's Bantamweight Champion. Known for her boxing skills and professionalism, she was a consistent top contender who helped establish credibility for women's MMA during its early growth period.

name: Sasha Banks
bio: The Boss who helped revolutionize women's wrestling in the modern era.

name: Scott Hall

name: Scott Steiner

name: Sgt. Slaughter

name: Shane Douglas
bio: The man who threw down the NWA Title and declared ECW a legitimate third alternative.

name: Shawn Michaels
bio: Shawn Michaels, 'The Heartbreak Kid' and 'Mr. WrestleMania,' is considered one of the greatest in-ring performers of all time. A founding member of D-Generation X and one half of The Rockers, HBK's athleticism, charisma, and storytelling ability made him a fan favorite. His ladder matches, Iron Man match, and retirement match are legendary.

name: Shayna Baszler
bio: Former MMA fighter who brought legitimate fighting credentials to WWE's women's division.

name: Sheamus

name: Sid Vicious
tagline: The Master and Ruler of the World

name: Solo Sikoa

name: Stan Hansen

name: Stan Stasiak

name: Steve Blackman

name: Sting

name: Stone Cold Steve Austin
bio: Steve Austin is an American retired professional wrestler, actor, producer, and television host.

name: Sugar Ray Leonard
bio: Sugar Ray Leonard was the face of boxing in the 1980s, combining exceptional skill with charisma and showmanship. He won world titles in five weight divisions and engaged in legendary rivalries with Roberto Duran, Thomas Hearns, and Marvin Hagler.

name: Sugar Ray Robinson
bio: Sugar Ray Robinson is often considered pound-for-pound the greatest boxer of all time. He held the world middleweight title five times and had a professional record of 173-19-6. Robinson was known for his hand speed, footwork, and ability to throw combinations from any angle.

name: Superfly Jimmy Snuka
bio: High-flying pioneer who revolutionized wrestling with his diving attacks from the top rope.

name: Superstar Billy Graham

name: Terry Funk

name: Test

name: Tetsuya Naito

name: The Dudley Boyz

bio: Tito Ortiz was one of the biggest stars in early UFC history and helped establish the light heavyweight division. Known for his wrestling background, ground-and-pound style, and larger-than-life personality, Ortiz was instrumental in the UFC's rise to mainstream popularity.

The longtime UFC Women's Flyweight Champion has defended her title multiple times with precision striking and tactical brilliance. She's considered one of the pound-for-pound best.
